It's with a heavy heart to hear the news of Amp Fiddler's passing. He wasn't just a musician; he was a true original in the music world, especially within hip-hop and soul. His impact was profound. Amp's collaborations brought a unique fusion of funk, soul, and electronic music, enriching the tapestry of modern sound. But it was his solo work that personally inspired me the most. His album "Waltz of a Ghetto Fly" was a revelation. The way he blended genres, creating soulful and cutting-edge music, showed me what was possible. If I recall correctly, @MocLiving borrowed that cd from me for a bit.

His impact on hip-hop is something I'll always revere. Introducing the Akai MPC to J Dilla, he didn't just change one artist's approach; he helped to revolutionized hip-hop production. His collaborations with Slum Village and others were a masterclass in blending soulful melodies with the raw energy of hip-hop. The music industry has lost a visionary, but Amp's teachings and influence should continue to resonate with us, even if we don't know it.

Rest in peace, @Amp_Fiddler . Your legacy will live on in the countless lives you've touched and the music you've left behind. You were a legend, a pioneer, and your spirit will forever be a part of the music we love and cherish.

It's about facing the toughest hurdles with perseverance and dedication.  Much of what I had accomplished I did in the shadows and while I celebrated a few here and there,  to me, they are more so distance memories. I've seen too many come and go since then, almost completely  breaking my heart and pulling me away from it all. But I'm here to finish what I  started, and I appreciate the team that has already been active and in motion,  as these goals are collaborative. Stay tuned.. or dont... I'll be moving forward regardless.

From the studio to your speakers, every album has a story.  At CMNWLTH, we're all about that story, especially when it's as rich as this one. Quality music? Check. Vibes with the artists? Double check. @KingdomKome and @che_uno bring more than just talent to the table - their dedication to music and work ethic are unparalleled. 

So, why remix an already amazing album? The answer is simple: We love to mix things up!  Cultural concepts, original sounds, and a connection to the artist's roots make it all the more special. And let's be honest, it's just super dope. 🔥 

Our mission at CMNWLTH is to not just release music, but to elevate it. First up, "Fernet Y Cola (Vago Remix)", a testament to our commitment to extraordinary sounds. This drops on 1/23/24, and thanks to @vago604's masterful remix skills. This isn't just a new album - it's a cultural odyssey, and they are setting new standards in music fusion. This is more than just a project for us; it's a celebration of innovation and cultural heritage. Tune into #TangoSessions by #LosChicosCriollos and #Vago
